{
  "text": "Now we create the Nates Galus service that enables instances and private subnets to access the Internet. The NAT gateway must be placed in a public subnet because it needs Internet connectivity itself. We're placing it in public subnet 1. The NAT gateway uses the Elastic IP we just created. When an instance in a private subnet makes an outbound request, the NAT gateway translates the private IP to its public Elastic IP, sends the request, and then translates the private subnet instances into medicated connections.",
